programmes.show_description: A driver who has crashed into another car passes a breath test but his behaviour is a cause for concern. And in Kent, a lorry crashes into a railway bridge and the driver runs off.
When a successful businessman discovers his partner has been having an affair, he is overcome with jealousy and a night in the pub ends in tragedy.
Dr Emma McMullen has her work cut out trying to help a patient with a challenging condition - and ends up needing a wipe down! And a patient's mole makes it hard to brush her hair.
After journalist Lisa Wallace receives a letter from her mother's killer, hinting at the kidnapping of another woman, she joins forces with Detective David Burkely to investigate. (Ep1)
Challengers 'Towel Compoulder' try to defeat the Eggheads to win the rolling prize fund. (Ep7)

We meet again with series favourites Bambi and Johnny. They've been busy since we last met them with a move along the Mediterranean to the beautiful, quiet coastal town of Huelva.
We meet Johnny Diamond, who, as his name suggests, is an absolute geezer and prides himself on having more front than Brighton.
The fight against the rise of shoplifting. In London's West End undercover officers pursue a known "dipper", and in Birmingham a stolen bank card scam becomes threatening. (Ep1)
Action-packed observational documentary series with Jamie Theakston. Alex and Jason chase down a gang of teenage suspects on foot through a housing estate.
Derbyshire police pursue criminals on the run, a suspect flees on foot, and there's a high-speed cross-border pursuit as a wanted man refuses to stop. Hosted by Jamie Theakston.
A fast and dangerous driver pushes the Traffic Cops to the limits, reaching speeds of over 150 mph. Action-packed observational documentary series with Jamie Theakston.
Four joyriders have a lucky escape from the wreckage of a Ford Mondeo and stolen property is found in the back of a vehicle. Action-packed documentary series.
Police race to intercept three men suspected of robbing a string of plumbers' merchants. A fleeing van speeds the wrong way round a major roundabout.
The officers intercept a stolen car, foil a cannabis grower, engage in a series of drugs raids and calm a drunken sailor. Series profiling the work of a high-speed police unit.
CCTV exposes the lies of a man who claims that a collision left him with serious injuries. Police crack a lost watch scam.
David leads a rescue operation. Tane and Levi risk their lives for love. Who will make it out of the trainwreck alive?
Multiple lives hang in the balance. Tane's in a life-and-death race against the clock. A Summer Bay favourite receives life-changing news.
Dr Amir Khan suspects that Jake's bloody cough could be TB. Varna's bloodshot eye could be acute glaucoma. Luke already has four children so he is in for a vasectomy.
Barnsley Casualty is facing one of its toughest shifts to date. With no children's beds available across the whole of Yorkshire, and a department filling up with children.
A motorist is stuck in his car, unable to move his legs, and may have suffered a serious spinal injury. A man in a hard-to-reach rural location has cut his leg with an angle grinder.
A patient is flown in by air ambulance after falling down a ditch with her mobility scooter; a woman is treated after impaling her eye on a tent peg and an ankle needs treatment.
In this sporty episode, a boxing coach has a lipoma that looks like an out-of-place ab, and a gym fanatic has lumps on his arms that friends have mistaken for odd-shaped muscles.
When dreams turn into plastic surgery nightmares. The show looks at dermal lip fillers and investigates how social media and celebs have driven a boom in the industry.
Dr Khan refers little Lucas to a specialist to explain his anaemia. Devon has suffered from gout in the past. Single mother Mamello is feeling very down and struggling to cope.
A two-year-old girl is brought in as she deals with dangerously low blood sugar levels; junior doctor Alex Chatburn has his own views on emergency admissions.
David goes to Castlemoy to continue the investigation. He and Detective Brennan chase a lead that pins Mark Bulger, an ex-con, to the kidnapping of a young woman. (Ep2)
In the quiz show, hosted by Jeremy Vine, challengers 'Shuttle Watchers' try to defeat the Eggheads to win the rolling prize fund. (Ep8)

Police stop an out-of-control driver whose passenger is a child without a seat belt. And there are tragic consequences when speed kills. Jamie Theakston presents.

The interceptors catch a gang of car thieves red-handed. Officers clamp down on car crime at Essex's biggest shopping centre.
